The Assistant Inspector General of Police (AIG), Zone 5, Benin, Lawan Jimeta Tanko, has decorated 51 newly promoted officers in Edo State with their new ranks. Decorating the officers at the Zone 5 headquarter, AIG Tanko said the 51 newly promoted inspectors comprised 42 males and nine females. He charged the officers to put in their best and be professional in the performance of their constitutional duty, show loyalty to the Nigeria Police Force (NPF) and consider themselves lucky to be so favoured by the Inspector General of Police (IGP), Usman Alkali Baba.